unmet

by what function does she hold
me if not sorcery, magic.
weaknesses of the mind and
the flesh. or the fear of non-
existence, alone ... lost
in a vast sea of emptiness,
sentenced to life without wiles?

there is no sympathy for
an inmate who is held inside
his prison without walls,
no guard, the cell door open
begging him to leave. he holds
himself captive.

such a broken man no longer
desires to be free. he has
no want to remain captive
however, either. he has died,
and longs for and fears
death all the same.

with his last meal he drinks
a cold and creamy glass of oat
milk and notes with every
sip that once consumed, there
will be no more.
